==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sensuality
<hw>Sen`su*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[CF. F.
<ets>sensualit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L. <ets>sensualitas</ets> sensibility,
capacity for sensation.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
sensual; devotedness to the gratification of the bodily appetites; free
indulgence in carnal or sensual pleasures; luxuriousness;
voluptuousness; lewdness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those pampered animals⟦br⟧
That rage in savage <qex>sensuality</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They avoid dress, lest they should have affections tainted by any
<qex>sensuality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sensualization</ent>⟦br⟧
